-- ONGC Offers 600,000 Barrels of Sudan Nile Blend Crude for February Loading
-- B y   Y e e   K a i   P i n
-- 2010-12-15T01:36:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-15/ongc-offers-600-000-barrels-of-sudan-nile-blend-crude-for-february-loading.html
Oil & Natural Gas Corp. , India’s
biggest explorer, is offering to sell 600,000 barrels of Nile
Blend crude from Sudan in February, according to a document e-
mailed to potential buyers.  ONGC Nile Ganga BV, the company’s Amsterdam-based unit,
will accept bids linked to the official selling price of
Indonesia’s  Minas  oil, the document showed. Nile Blend, a low-
sulfur grade, is produced by Greater Nile Petroleum Operating
Co., in which ONGC has a 25 percent stake.  Details of the offer are as follow:  To contact the reporter on this story:
